title: Oil dips on well supplied markets despite tighter Iran sanctions
text: Oil prices inched lower on Wednesday on signs that global markets remain adequately supplied despite a jump to 2019 highs this week on Washington's push for tighter sanctions against Iran.

title: Why the Japanese don't buy American cars
text: U.S. automakers barely have a presence in Japan, the world's third-largest car market. Some blame protectionism, others cite the tastes of Japanese consumers and a lack of investment.

title: Foxconn and Wisconsin are renegotiating their massive factory deal, governor's letter reveals
text: The disclosure comes in a letter from Governor Tony Evers to Foxconn executive Louis Woo, a special assistant to Chairman Terry Gou and the company's point person on the project.

title: Markets are at new highs, but the euphoria is missing
text: Stock traders do not view a new high as truly valid unless there is some serious action. And that is what is missing from the rally.

title: After Chilly Winter, Homebuilders To Share Earnings With High Hopes Ahead
text: The home building and home supply sectors are preparing to report Q1 results in coming weeks, but may have struggled in part due to chilly winter weather.

title: Pharma distributor Rochester Drug agrees to pay $20 million in first criminal opioid case
text: The indictment marked the first ever federal criminal charges against company executives for conspiring to illegally distribute opioids.

title: LGBT groups and tech companies warn that a Texas bill could cost the state billions
text: The LGBTQ community and major employers say a bill passed by the Texas Senate is a license to discriminate, giving professionals the right to turn away people based on religious beliefs. Amazon, Dell, Apple and Facebook urged Texas to drop the bill.

title: How To Get An Early Piece Of The Next Big IPO
text: Wish you could get in early before the next big tech IPO? If a call to the CEO falls flat, maybe Forge can help.

title: Cannabis PR Firm Mattio Communications Completes Seed Round
text: Mattio Communications, a cannabis marketing company, said Tuesday it completed its seed round of funding that included a number of high profile venture capital firms.

title: Alternative data comes of age, and investors are noticing
text: The ubiquity of the Internet of Things, coupled with improvements in data analytics means insights are available to investors earlier than ever. Mainstream investors are noticing.

title: Algorithmic Trading: What It Means For Stock Market Volatility And Individual Investors
text: When the stock market turns volatile, algorithmic trading often gets the blame. Here's what investors need to know about algo trading and how it works.

title: Another Covered Call ETF Arrives
text: Writing covered calls is a popular options strategy used by income investors. Also known as a “buy-write” strategy, covered calls involve selling call options on a stock the investor already owns.

title: Wealthfront's new high-yield accounts bring in $1 billion in just a few months
text: Wealthfront's high-yield cash account has attracted $1 billion from customers since launching in February.

title: Autonomous aircraft designed for 'ultra-endurance' flights reaches milestone
text: A self-sufficient autonomous aircraft that could potentially embark on flights of an indefinite length has reached a development milestone, academics said on Tuesday.

title: KeepTruckin Rolls Into A $149M Series D Round
text: KeepTruckin, a trucking technology provider, today announced it secured $149 million in a Series D investment led by Greenoaks Capital, with participation from existing investors IVP, GV, Index Ventures and Scale Venture Partners.

title: Beyond Meat Gets Aboard the IPO Bandwagon
text: The plant-based meat maker has filed a revised S-1. It hopes to raise $184 million in its public debut.

title: AI Will Be A Vital Tool In Making The Global Economy More Sustainable And Efficient - PwC
text: Artificial intelligence can play a powerful role in making the global economy more sustainable, through better monitoring, predicting problems in advance, and enabling the more efficient use of resources.

title: U.S. Will Try To Zero Out Iranian Oil Exports As It Chooses Not To Extend Waivers; Prices Up In Response
text: Prices on Monday did rise sharply as would be expected following the late Sunday news.

title: Locus Robotics Raises $26 Million In Series C Round
text: The round brings the total amount of money Locus has raised since launching in 2014 to $66 million.

title: Talking money with Suzy Welch: 'You don't have to be an expert to get into the market'
text: Investing is a great way to grow your money, but the fear of not knowing enough about the market and losing money tends to scare people off. But life management expert Suzy Welch says you don't need to be an expert to win big.

title: Bekaert: Refinancing Debt With Declining EBITDA And Free Cash Flow Will Be Tough
text: The dividend got cut to 0.70 EUR per share, but perhaps the money should have been used to reduce the debt ratio?

title: Stocks Mixed As Earnings Ramp Up; Oil Extends Gain: Markets Wrap
text: European stocks slipped, U.S. equity index futures were range bound and Asian shares were mixed on Tuesday as many markets reopened after a long weekend.

title: Why Fintech Should Embrace The Fourth Industrial Revolution
text: A recent report from the World Economic Forum highlighted why financial services should welcome what has been dubbed the “fourth industrial revolution” after the impact it has had on a range of sectors such as healthcare, retail and agriculture.

title: Thomas Cook shares rise on report of possible takeover
text: Thomas Cook had put its airline business up for sale and closed stores this year, following a heat-wave in northern Europe last summer.

title: Goldman Sachs is not expecting oil to rally despite the US tightening sanctions on Iran
text: Goldman Sachs expects the United States' decision to end exemptions from sanctions for countries still buying oil from Iran to have a limited impact on crude prices.

title: Some international banks are finally seeing their China investments pay off
text: UBS, Invesco and J.P. Morgan topped Shanghai-based Z-Ben Advisors’ annual rankings.
